    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The syntax for setting quoted and decorated lines both use a colon to separate the directives from optional modifiers.  Since the colon under Windows may be part of a hard path (e.g., C:\\my\\path\\file) we must consider this when looking for the right colon.  This PR will, under WIN32, only recognize the colon in position j if there is at least one more character and that one is not a slash or backslash, and that the previous character is not a letter.  This should skip d:\\path is a contender.\r\n\r\nThis section happens twice in gmt_init.c with a slight variation of initialization so this PR also delegates this search to a local function that is now called in both places.\r\n\r\nWill required @joa-quim to test this under Windows.\r\n",
